Class-Pluggability

This module provides a basic framework for defining plugin-based classes and their plugins based on attributes.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Class::Pluggability

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Class-Pluggability

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Class-Pluggability

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Class-Pluggability

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Class-Pluggability

